# Velxon / AI Orchestrator — Cline Rules

## Project Stack
- TypeScript (tsconfig.json present)
- Node.js scripts in scripts/
- Agents defined in agents/*.md
- Skills defined in skills/

## Coding Pipeline

For any non-trivial coding task, run the pipeline script — it handles triage, planning, coding, and review automatically via Ollama:

```bash
bash scripts/run_pipeline.sh "<task description>"
```

Wait for it to finish, then show the user the output. Do NOT manually replicate the pipeline steps — the script does it all.

For simple single-file edits, make the change directly without the pipeline.

## Agent Trigger Rules

Read the corresponding agent file before acting on these tasks:

| Task type | Agent file to read |
|---|---|
| Planning, architecture, approach | `agents/planner.md` |
| Writing code, implementing features | `agents/coder.md` |
| Code review, quality check | `agents/reviewer.md` |
| Git commit, PR, staging | `agents/commit.md` |
| Bug fix, root cause analysis | `agents/debugger.md` |
| System design, refactoring | `agents/architect.md` |
| CI/CD, Docker, deployment | `agents/devops.md` |
| Documentation | `agents/doc-writer.md` |
| Security audit | `agents/security-auditor.md` |
| Tests | `agents/qa-orchestrator.md` |

## Skills (load when relevant)

| Area | Skill file |
|---|---|
| TypeScript standards | `skills/ts-code-standarts.md` |
| API design | `skills/api-design-patterns/SKILL.md` |
| Docker | `skills/docker-best-practices/SKILL.md` |
| CI/CD | `skills/ci-cd-pipelines/SKILL.md` |
| LLM integration | `skills/llm-integration/SKILL.md` |
| Security | `skills/security-hardening/SKILL.md` |

## Key Constraints

- Never edit `.sh` scripts directly — use the coder agent workflow
- Never add npm/Python dependencies without explicit approval
- Always use `jq` for JSON processing in shell scripts
- Context files go in `.claude/context/`
- Never commit directly to main — use feature branches

## Project Structure (key paths)

```
agents/       — agent instructions
skills/       — coding standards & expertise
scripts/      — shell automation
src/          — TypeScript source
tickets/      — task tickets
.claude/      — Claude Code config and context
```
